It&rsquo;s quite easy to use text files as input source or to redirect the output of programs to files if you happen to do programming on a unix/linux terminal.
Let&rsquo;s take an example of a usual random number generator:
// random.c #include &lt;stdio.h&gt;#include &lt;stdlib.h&gt;int main () { int i, count=99999999; for (i = 0; i &lt; count; i += 1) printf(&#34;%d\n&#34;, (int)random()); return 0; } Let&rsquo;s generate an executable by the name random.

